In [202]:
from skimage.measure import regionprops

tile_size = 101

X = np.zeros([num_super,tile_size,tile_size,3])
y = np.zeros([num_super,7])

i = 0
for prop in regionprops(res_slic):
    # rounding, who cares
    ix, iy = np.int_(prop.centroid)
    
    _label = labels[ix,iy]
    # should pad here:
    if ix < tile_size/2 or ix > core_image.shape[0] - tile_size/2:
        continue
    if iy < tile_size/2 or iy > core_image.shape[1] - tile_size/2:
        continue

    X[i,:,:,:] = core_image[ix-tile_size//2:ix+tile_size//2+1,
                            iy-tile_size//2:iy+tile_size//2+1]
    y[i,_label] = 1
    
    i += 1
    
X = X[:i,...]
y = y[:i,...]

# discard null
indx = y[:,0] != 1
X = X[indx,...]
y = y[indx,...]

y = y[:,1:]

In [210]:
from keras.models import Model
from keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, BatchNormalization, Flatten
from keras.optimizers import SGD

def create_model():
    
    vgg16_model = VGG16(include_top=False,input_shape=(tile_size,tile_size,3))
    # don't re-train it
    for layer in vgg16_model.layers:
        layer.trainable = False
    
    layers = vgg16_model.output

    layers = Flatten()(layers)
    # normalize things
    layers = BatchNormalization()(layers)
    # 
    layers = Dropout(0.5)(layers)
    layers = Dense(8, activation='relu')(layers)
    layers = Dense(6, activation='softmax')(layers)

    # our new model:
    model = Model(vgg16_model.input, layers)
    #model.summary()

    # compile
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy',
                      optimizer=SGD(lr=1e-3, decay=1e-5, momentum=0.9),
                      metrics=['accuracy'])

    
    return model
In [262]:
from keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from keras.applications.vgg16 import preprocess_input
from keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping
#
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold



earlystopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, min_delta=0.01)
batch_size = 32

# we have very limited data, so augment it
aug = ImageDataGenerator(preprocessing_function=preprocess_input,
                       featurewise_center=True,
                       featurewise_std_normalization=True,
                       rotation_range=90.,
                       width_shift_range=0.2,
                       height_shift_range=0.2,
                       zoom_range=0.2,
                       fill_mode='reflect')

cvscores = []
models = []
for train, test in KFold(n_splits=5, random_state=42).split(X):

    model = create_model()
    
    X_train, y_train = X[train,...], y[train,...]
    X_test, y_test = X[test,...], y[test,...]
    
    aug.fit(X_train)
    X_test = aug.standardize(X_test)
    
    model.fit_generator(
                aug.flow(X,y,batch_size=32),
                validation_data=(X_test,y_test),
                steps_per_epoch=2*X.shape[0]//batch_size,
                epochs=100,
                callbacks=[earlystopping], verbose=0)
    
    models.append(model)
    
    scores = model.evaluate(X_test, y_test, verbose=0)
    print("%s: %.2f%%" % (model.metrics_names[1], scores[1]*100))
    cvscores.append(scores[1] * 100)
# assuming the training is representative of the data at large, our expectations:
print("%.2f%% (+/- %.2f%%)" % (np.mean(cvscores), np.std(cvscores)))

from skimage.measure import regionprops

Xp = np.zeros([num_super,tile_size,tile_size,3])
coord = []

i = 0
for prop in regionprops(res_slic):
    
    ix, iy = np.int_(prop.centroid)
    
    # should pad here:
    if ix < tile_size/2 or ix > core_image.shape[0] - tile_size/2:
        continue
    if iy < tile_size/2 or iy > core_image.shape[1] - tile_size/2:
        continue
        
    # slic is zero bases
    rp = prop.label 
    coord.append(rp)
    
    Xp[i,:,:,:] = core_image[ix-tile_size//2:ix+tile_size//2+1,
                             iy-tile_size//2:iy+tile_size//2+1]
    
    i += 1
    
Xp = Xp[:i,...]

aug.fit(X)
Xp = aug.standardize(Xp)

    for ix, iy in props[rp-1].coords:
        proba[ix,iy,:] = yp[i,:]
